abstract = {Bus terminals are mega structures designed to handle large volume of buses and passenger traffic. The study analysed the structures and materials used for construction of bus terminals from various Indian states and compared with various global standards focused on creating standards for usage of materials for construction with architectural aspects, structural response and able to fulfill the needs of the stakeholders. The study covers major bus stations in India and other countries like UK, Turkey, Malaysia and USA. Following a review of the situation as it stands, subsequent research takes into account various bus terminal designs from around the world. The examination includes a comprehensive review of urban, architectural, and structural approaches, as well as current global trends in terminal design. The link between structural design and architectural expression is the focus of the analysis. The intention is to demonstrate how the operation ability of bus terminals is dependent on functional characteristics that are influenced by architectural expression and structural systems, including their influence on the creation of memorable and observable landmarks. Few materials were suggested in the study for bus terminus constructions such as shape memory alloys, piezoelectric materials, smart concrete for large structures like terminal buildings and single/double decked bus parking, etc. It helps the architects and transit planners to design the bus terminus as per global standards design in India.}
}
